real direction or purpose,

00:01:34.690 --> 00:01:36.320 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of stress,
and a lot of fear.

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:40.300 align:middle line:84%
I had a good family, good
parenting, a good household.

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:41.950 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what it was from.

00:01:41.950 --> 00:01:44.490 align:middle line:90%
But I ended up going to college.

00:01:44.490 --> 00:01:47.842 align:middle line:84%
And I started college
because I was just

00:01:47.842 --> 00:01:49.550 align:middle line:84%
told that's what you
were supposed to do.

00:01:49.550 --> 00:01:49.805 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:01:49.805 --> 00:01:50.470 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: And I got into
the middle of my first year.

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:55.120 align:middle line:84%
And before my first
year was over,

00:01:55.120 --> 00:01:57.960 align:middle line:84%
I was asked to leave the college
because I was academically

00:01:57.960 --> 00:02:01.420 align:middle line:90%
ineligible with a 0.57 GPA.

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:02.120 align:middle line:90%
0.57.

00:02:02.120 --> 00:02:03.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow, OK.

00:02:03.690 --> 00:02:04.940 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: So I was basically--

00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:05.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where was this?

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:90%
In the Midwest?

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.290 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: This was
in the Midwest.

00:02:07.290 --> 00:02:07.790 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:10.229 align:middle line:84%
And so I was actually
kicked out of college

00:02:10.229 --> 00:02:11.770 align:middle line:84%
because my grades
weren't good enough

00:02:11.770 --> 00:02:14.030 align:middle line:84%
to continue by the
end of my first year.

00:02:14.030 --> 00:02:16.960 align:middle line:84%
And so I started taking
minimum wage jobs.

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:20.494 align:middle line:84%
I fumbled from one minimum wage
job to the next, just living

00:02:20.494 --> 00:02:21.160 align:middle line:90%
for the weekend.

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:22.860 align:middle line:90%
I had no direction, no purpose.

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:25.780 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know who I was
or where I was going.

00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:30.900 align:middle line:84%
And I was in my mid 20s,
and at my latest job.

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And I was in a steel
and aluminum fabrication

00:02:33.170 --> 00:02:35.070 align:middle line:90%
factory covered in grease.

00:02:35.070 --> 00:02:36.590 align:middle line:90%
And I was standing there.

00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:38.600 align:middle line:84%
And one day, something
just came over me.

00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:42.310 align:middle line:90%
And it was like I just woke up.

00:02:42.310 --> 00:02:44.590 align:middle line:84%
And there was a surge
of energy in me.

00:02:44.590 --> 00:02:46.050 align:middle line:90%
There was a clarity in me.

00:02:46.050 --> 00:02:48.031 align:middle line:90%
There was a confidence in me.

00:02:48.031 --> 00:02:49.530 align:middle line:84%
The way I describe
it, it was like I

00:02:49.530 --> 00:02:51.960 align:middle line:90%
had this view from 50,000 feet.

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:56.050 align:middle line:84%
And I could see my entire
life, how it had led me there.

00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:57.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was there anything
that had happened?

00:02:57.930 --> 00:02:58.679 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Nothing.

00:02:58.679 --> 00:03:00.820 align:middle line:84%
There was no
precipitating event.

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.800 align:middle line:84%
And that was part of what
put me on this journey

00:03:03.800 --> 00:03:08.000 align:middle line:84%
is because it was just like I
had this surge of confidence,

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.104 align:middle line:84%
and clarity, and knowing that my
life was going to be radically

00:03:12.104 --> 00:03:13.520 align:middle line:84%
different from
that point forward.

00:03:13.520 --> 00:03:16.350 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was a
foregone conclusion.

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:18.760 align:middle line:84%
It was only a question of
how was that going to happen.

00:03:18.760 --> 00:03:21.054 align:middle line:90%
And I left the job right then.

00:03:21.054 --> 00:03:22.470 align:middle line:84%
And I went and I
got on the phone.

00:03:22.470 --> 00:03:25.219 align:middle line:84%
And earlier in my life, I
had had a positive healing

00:03:25.219 --> 00:03:26.510 align:middle line:90%
experience with a chiropractor.

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:27.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:03:27.570 --> 00:03:30.300 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: So I was just
looking at a path for me.

00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:33.970 align:middle line:84%
And I thought well,
that's going to be a step.

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And I called the
chiropractic college.

00:03:36.660 --> 00:03:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And they, of course,
said well, it's

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.860 align:middle line:84%
a four-year
postgraduate program.

00:03:40.860 --> 00:03:42.240 align:middle line:90%
It's a doctoral program.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And so you're not getting
in with your 0.57 first year

00:03:45.690 --> 00:03:46.690 align:middle line:90%
of college.

00:03:46.690 --> 00:03:48.540 align:middle line:90%
So they gave me some direction.

00:03:48.540 --> 00:03:50.880 align:middle line:84%
And I found a college
that would take me.

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:52.210 align:middle line:90%
And I enrolled in classes.

00:03:52.210 --> 00:03:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And by then, I was just
on fire with passion.

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:57.470 align:middle line:84%
And I just aced
all of my classes.

00:03:57.470 --> 00:03:57.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:03:57.990 --> 00:04:00.450 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: I started taking
32 credit hours a semester,

00:04:00.450 --> 00:04:03.040 align:middle line:84%
more than twice the
normal load of physics,

00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:04.175 align:middle line:90%
and chemistry, and biology.

00:04:04.175 --> 00:04:05.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was it because
you were finally

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:07.530 align:middle line:90%
interested in something?

00:04:07.530 --> 00:04:10.000 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Yes, but it
was more than that.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:11.400 align:middle line:84%
Whatever happened
inside of me is

00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:12.922 align:middle line:84%
what got me interested
in something.

00:04:12.922 --> 00:04:13.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It switched on.

00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Right.

00:04:14.180 --> 00:04:15.346 align:middle line:90%
Something switched on in me.

00:04:15.346 --> 00:04:17.760 align:middle line:90%
And I know now what that is.

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:20.980 align:middle line:84%
I know that the dormant part
of the higher brain engaged.

00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:22.252 align:middle line:90%
But, at the time, I didn't.

00:04:22.252 --> 00:04:24.900 align:middle line:84%
I just knew I had
dramatically changed.

00:04:24.900 --> 00:04:27.140 align:middle line:90%
And so I aced all of my classes.

00:04:27.140 --> 00:04:28.750 align:middle line:84%
I got into the
professional school.

00:04:28.750 --> 00:04:32.360 align:middle line:84%
I did the four-year doctoral
program in three years

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:33.830 align:middle line:90%
on an accelerated program.

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:36.177 align:middle line:84%
I graduated with honors on
the National Deans List.

00:04:36.177 --> 00:04:38.755 align:middle line:84%
And I say all of this because
that had not been my history.

00:04:38.755 --> 00:04:39.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It wasn't the case.

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:41.655 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: It was not the case.

00:04:41.655 --> 00:04:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And so that set me
on this path of I

00:04:45.420 --> 00:04:49.130 align:middle line:84%
got just incredibly
curious about why me?

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:49.970 align:middle line:90%
What was that?

00:04:49.970 --> 00:04:51.290 align:middle line:90%
Why did that happen?

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:54.880 align:middle line:84%
Why did my life
change so dramatic?

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:57.550 align:middle line:84%
And so that studying
human potential

00:04:57.550 --> 00:04:59.370 align:middle line:84%
and human
transformation basically

00:04:59.370 --> 00:05:02.280 align:middle line:84%
become my life's passion,
and my life's work,

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:04.024 align:middle line:90%
and still is today.

00:05:04.024 --> 00:05:06.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you wanted to
find out why that happened?

00:05:06.190 --> 00:05:06.510 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Yeah.

00:05:06.510 --> 00:05:07.957 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And where did you go?

00:05:07.957 --> 00:05:09.915 align:middle line:84%
I mean, obviously you
went down this long path,

00:05:09.915 --> 00:05:11.290 align:middle line:84%
but where did you
go to find out?

00:05:11.290 --> 00:05:12.401 align:middle line:90%
What was that moment?

00:05:12.401 --> 00:05:13.900 align:middle line:84%
What was that turning
point for you?

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:16.290 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Well, what I
started doing was just

00:05:16.290 --> 00:05:20.520 align:middle line:84%
devouring everything that I
could possibly read, or study,

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.010 align:middle line:84%
or participate in
that had anything

00:05:23.010 --> 00:05:24.810 align:middle line:84%
to do with personal
transformation,

00:05:24.810 --> 00:05:30.210 align:middle line:84%
with self-help, with the
evolution of consciousness,

00:05:30.210 --> 00:05:34.110 align:middle line:84%
Eastern philosophies,
Western philosophies.

00:05:34.110 --> 00:05:36.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I just spent my
life studying all of it

00:05:36.680 --> 00:05:39.560 align:middle line:84%
and then starting to learn
different energy work

00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:40.080 align:middle line:90%
techniques.

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:42.960 align:middle line:84%
And I started, through
my chiropractic training,

00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:45.560 align:middle line:84%
then getting involved
in different quasi-type

00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:47.990 align:middle line:84%
chiropractic techniques
and energy techniques.

00:05:47.990 --> 00:05:51.610 align:middle line:84%
NSA care was one of them
that had a lot of influence.

00:05:51.610 --> 00:05:56.100 align:middle line:84%
And so one of the things that
I found in my search that was

00:05:56.100 --> 00:06:01.310 align:middle line:84%
somewhat disturbing was
that what happened to me--

00:06:01.310 --> 00:06:05.340 align:middle line:84%
I actually studied 5,000-year
history of personal growth

00:06:05.340 --> 00:06:07.120 align:middle line:90%
and transformation.

00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:11.750 align:middle line:84%
And I found lots of
references to this kind

00:06:11.750 --> 00:06:12.580 align:middle line:90%
of thing happening.

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:16.570 align:middle line:84%
Or even people would report like
the enlightenment experience

00:06:16.570 --> 00:06:18.100 align:middle line:90%
and that type of thing.

00:06:18.100 --> 00:06:19.680 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting
thing from all

00:06:19.680 --> 00:06:21.930 align:middle line:84%
of the literature, all of
the techniques I studied,

00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:26.740 align:middle line:84%
and all of the data was that
it didn't happen very often.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:28.520 align:middle line:84%
It didn't happen to
very many people.

00:06:28.520 --> 00:06:32.185 align:middle line:84%
It was very inconsistent and
was often not sustainable.

00:06:32.185 --> 00:06:35.970 align:middle line:84%
And even these techniques that
could lead to dramatic change,

00:06:35.970 --> 00:06:37.570 align:middle line:84%
it was like 1 out
of 1,000 people

00:06:37.570 --> 00:06:39.400 align:middle line:84%
that it would
actually happen with.

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:43.460 align:middle line:84%
And so it got me really trying
to figure out why was that?

00:06:43.460 --> 00:06:45.360 align:middle line:84%
If it was possible
for me, if even

00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:46.890 align:middle line:84%
maybe even more
dramatic things were

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:48.247 align:middle line:90%
possible for other people--

00:06:48.247 --> 00:06:48.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:06:48.830 --> 00:06:51.210 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: --in the
literature, then

00:06:51.210 --> 00:06:53.910 align:middle line:84%
why wasn't it possible for
everyone, or why couldn't it

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:55.630 align:middle line:90%
happen all the time?

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:59.500 align:middle line:84%
And what I know now, what
I'm convinced of now,

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:02.720 align:middle line:84%
is that the missing
link in all of this

00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:08.300 align:middle line:84%
is that the literal brain
has to change for our life

00:07:08.300 --> 00:07:09.900 align:middle line:84%
to change in those
dramatic ways.

00:07:09.900 --> 00:07:12.130 align:middle line:84%
That we have to be
able to get energy

00:07:12.130 --> 00:07:15.150 align:middle line:84%
into this new-evolved,
untapped part of our brain,

00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:17.140 align:middle line:90%
the prefrontal cortex.

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:19.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now did
you equate this

00:07:19.090 --> 00:07:20.600 align:middle line:84%
to a spiritual
experience at all?

00:07:20.600 --> 00:07:24.040 align:middle line:84%
Did you find that it was a
religious epiphany at all,

00:07:24.040 --> 00:07:26.680 align:middle line:90%
or was it just a clarity?

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:29.260 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: At the time, I
didn't really-- I mean, all

00:07:29.260 --> 00:07:33.670 align:middle line:84%
I knew was that I had
an energy inside of me.

00:07:33.670 --> 00:07:35.730 align:middle line:90%
I had a passion inside of me.

00:07:35.730 --> 00:07:37.430 align:middle line:90%
I had a confidence inside of me.

00:07:37.430 --> 00:07:40.300 align:middle line:84%
And I had a clarity inside of
me that I had never had before.

00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:42.310 align:middle line:84%
And it was like
it just turned on.

00:07:42.310 --> 00:07:46.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And now you have now
then equated this to the brain.

00:07:46.030 --> 00:07:47.640 align:middle line:84%
Explain, if you
can, the difference

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:50.510 align:middle line:84%
between the lower-brain thinking
and the higher-brain thinking,

00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:52.214 align:middle line:84%
the primitive and the
prefrontal cortex.

00:07:52.214 --> 00:07:52.880 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Right.

00:07:52.880 --> 00:07:55.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's even more
than just thinking.

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:58.750 align:middle line:84%
Those brains really kind
of drive our behavior even.

00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:01.640 align:middle line:84%
And so thinking
absolutely is part of it.

00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:03.680 align:middle line:84%
In fact, just to
back up a second,

00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:08.270 align:middle line:84%
here's a really good way
to kind of understand

00:08:08.270 --> 00:08:10.950 align:middle line:84%
the need for getting energy
into that higher brain,

00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:12.900 align:middle line:84%
and why so many
