And so you asked me what's
the difference in the lower

00:08:54.406 --> 00:08:55.530 align:middle line:90%
brain and the higher brain?

00:08:55.530 --> 00:09:00.360 align:middle line:84%
And so that lower brain
is a very primitive part

00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:01.490 align:middle line:90%
of our brain.

00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:03.830 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people don't
know this, but the brain

00:09:03.830 --> 00:09:07.930 align:middle line:84%
is actually evolved
in stages, in layers.

00:09:07.930 --> 00:09:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And the early stage
is what we generically

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:13.560 align:middle line:90%
call this lower brain.

00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:17.640 align:middle line:84%
And its job is to protect you
in a predator-rich environment.

00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.295 align:middle line:84%
Its job is to keep you from
being eaten by a tiger.

00:09:20.295 --> 00:09:22.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In the caveman days, and
that's what we needed to have.

00:09:22.920 --> 00:09:23.970 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: That's right.

00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:24.830 align:middle line:90%
It was fight or flight.

00:09:24.830 --> 00:09:26.329 align:middle line:84%
It was how do I get
through the day?

00:09:26.329 --> 00:09:29.850 align:middle line:84%
How do I survive in this
hostile, predator-rich world?

00:09:29.850 --> 00:09:32.050 align:middle line:90%
That's all that's important, OK?

00:09:32.050 --> 00:09:35.080 align:middle line:84%
Spiritual connection,
and purpose, and growth,

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:39.190 align:middle line:84%
and evolution, and finding
your potential-- that's

00:09:39.190 --> 00:09:40.974 align:middle line:84%
not important when
you have to survive,

00:09:40.974 --> 00:09:43.390 align:middle line:84%
when you have to find food,
and you have to not get eaten.

00:09:43.390 --> 00:09:43.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:44.380 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:44.380 --> 00:09:46.760 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: And so
that lower brain

00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:50.030 align:middle line:84%
was in the species for
a very, very long time.

00:09:50.030 --> 00:09:52.160 align:middle line:90%
And it's still in the species.

00:09:52.160 --> 00:09:55.240 align:middle line:84%
It's not changed since
caveman days, OK?

00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:58.967 align:middle line:84%
What's happened is layers build
over that old lower brain.

00:09:58.967 --> 00:10:00.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Through evolution.

00:10:00.050 --> 00:10:01.240 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Through evolution.

00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:04.030 align:middle line:84%
And now we have--
the latest emergent

00:10:04.030 --> 00:10:05.990 align:middle line:84%
is this prefrontal
cortex, this highest,

00:10:05.990 --> 00:10:07.450 align:middle line:90%
most evolved part of our brain.

00:10:07.450 --> 00:10:09.335 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the researcher
Paul MacLean,

00:10:09.335 --> 00:10:13.210 align:middle line:84%
who's the one-- who was
one of the first ones

00:10:13.210 --> 00:10:16.960 align:middle line:84%
to really tease out these
discrete layers of brain

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:20.790 align:middle line:84%
development, he refers
to those frontal lobes

00:10:20.790 --> 00:10:22.770 align:middle line:84%
and that prefrontal
cortex as the angel

00:10:22.770 --> 00:10:25.170 align:middle line:84%
lobes because that's the
part of the brain where

00:10:25.170 --> 00:10:27.637 align:middle line:84%
we have that high-end
human experience.

00:10:27.637 --> 00:10:28.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:10:28.470 --> 00:10:31.145 align:middle line:84%
So when we had the industrial
age, and now the technology

00:10:31.145 --> 00:10:34.987 align:middle line:84%
age, did that make significant
impacts on those layers

00:10:34.987 --> 00:10:36.070 align:middle line:90%
that you're talking about?

00:10:36.070 --> 00:10:38.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we didn't just go
from primitive to higher.

00:10:38.890 --> 00:10:41.150 align:middle line:84%
Did the steps in between
have to do with this?

00:10:41.150 --> 00:10:42.840 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Oh, man, are you
ever speaking my language.

00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:43.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:10:43.190 --> 00:10:43.800 align:middle line:90%
I love this.

00:10:43.800 --> 00:10:44.300 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:44.860 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:48.110 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: No, that's
a very, very apt--

00:10:48.110 --> 00:10:52.020 align:middle line:84%
those are some dots that I
have connected through this.

00:10:52.020 --> 00:10:54.310 align:middle line:84%
And I was going to talk
about this a little later,

00:10:54.310 --> 00:10:58.150 align:middle line:84%
but maybe this is a good
place to jump into it.

00:10:58.150 --> 00:11:01.160 align:middle line:84%
So just real quick about the
lower brain, higher brain.

00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:04.910 align:middle line:84%
So the lower part of the
brain, that is where stress

00:11:04.910 --> 00:11:05.650 align:middle line:90%
is produced.

00:11:05.650 --> 00:11:08.570 align:middle line:84%
It's designed to keep
us from being eaten, OK?

00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:12.216 align:middle line:84%
And it's the same in
us today as it was back

00:11:12.216 --> 00:11:13.840 align:middle line:84%
when the environment
was predator-rich.

00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:14.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because
it's unconscious.

00:11:14.710 --> 00:11:15.835 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: It's unconscious.

00:11:15.835 --> 00:11:19.820 align:middle line:84%
But now we've evolved these
higher brain structures,

00:11:19.820 --> 00:11:23.290 align:middle line:84%
but the problem is the research
tells us they're latent,

00:11:23.290 --> 00:11:24.530 align:middle line:90%
they're dormant.

00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:29.240 align:middle line:84%
The prefrontal cortex is used--
5% to 10% of its potential

00:11:29.240 --> 00:11:32.090 align:middle line:84%
is all that's really
used in humanity, OK?

00:11:32.090 --> 00:11:34.430 align:middle line:84%
And so there's this
untapped potential.

00:11:34.430 --> 00:11:38.270 align:middle line:84%
It's like we evolved, we
emerged the structure,

00:11:38.270 --> 00:11:42.080 align:middle line:84%
but we haven't got the energy
in it, and molded it in a way,

00:11:42.080 --> 00:11:44.500 align:middle line:84%
and are able to
metabolize it in a way,

00:11:44.500 --> 00:11:46.910 align:middle line:84%
and live from
there consistently.

00:11:46.910 --> 00:11:51.970 align:middle line:84%
And so the beautiful
point that you just made

00:11:51.970 --> 00:11:54.450 align:middle line:84%
is that actually
human civilization

00:11:54.450 --> 00:11:57.230 align:middle line:84%
has gone through five
major transformations.

00:11:57.230 --> 00:11:59.940 align:middle line:84%
There's a couple of
different models of this.

00:11:59.940 --> 00:12:01.940 align:middle line:84%
One of them that's
easy to explain

00:12:01.940 --> 00:12:04.630 align:middle line:84%
is the great
historian Jean Gebser

00:12:04.630 --> 00:12:08.670 align:middle line:84%
who has measured these
five discrete layers of--

00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:09.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Human evolution.

00:12:09.690 --> 00:12:13.080 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Of human evolution,
of cultural evolution, culture

00:12:13.080 --> 00:12:15.545 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness over
the last 100,000 years.

00:12:15.545 --> 00:12:16.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:19.760 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: And they've gone from
this archaic, fight or flight

00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:22.980 align:middle line:84%
into a magic, into a
mythic, into a rational,

00:12:22.980 --> 00:12:25.270 align:middle line:84%
which you're calling
technological-- he calls

00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:28.070 align:middle line:84%
the rational, or mental
structure-- and then

00:12:28.070 --> 00:12:31.540 align:middle line:84%
into this postmodern
humanistic stage that we're

00:12:31.540 --> 00:12:32.560 align:middle line:90%
kind of all a part of.

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:34.101 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So I just
want to grasp this.

00:12:34.101 --> 00:12:36.380 align:middle line:84%
So magic, mythics, you
have Plato, Hipocrates,

00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:38.144 align:middle line:84%
all of those in the
magic, mythic, and--

00:12:38.144 --> 00:12:39.560 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Well,
they were actually

00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:43.380 align:middle line:84%
early examples of this
rational stage of development.

00:12:43.380 --> 00:12:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Ancient Greece was one
of the first flourishings

00:12:46.390 --> 00:12:48.407 align:middle line:84%
of this rational
mental structure,

00:12:48.407 --> 00:12:49.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:12:49.240 --> 00:12:51.460 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: Or stage of
consciousness and culture.

00:12:51.460 --> 00:12:52.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I would think so.

00:12:52.510 --> 00:12:52.770 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:12:52.770 --> 00:12:53.560 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: Yeah.

00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:58.540 align:middle line:84%
So what I am suggesting, and
the point that you kind of

00:12:58.540 --> 00:13:02.950 align:middle line:84%
intuitively captured there
is that these stages-- each

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:06.130 align:middle line:84%
of these stages of
consciousness evolution

00:13:06.130 --> 00:13:12.000 align:middle line:84%
have produced more care, more
compassion, more love, more

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:12.800 align:middle line:90%
consciousness.

00:13:12.800 --> 00:13:15.465 align:middle line:84%
That's been a hallmark of this
evolution of consciousness over

00:13:15.465 --> 00:13:20.730 align:middle line:84%
a 100,000-year year period in
cultures and in individuals.

00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And so what I am suggesting
is that it correlates

00:13:25.760 --> 00:13:27.890 align:middle line:84%
with these layers
of brain development

00:13:27.890 --> 00:13:30.930 align:middle line:84%
that have been layed down
through biological evolution.

00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:31.439 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:13:31.439 --> 00:13:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: And so that
there's relationships

00:13:33.230 --> 00:13:35.120 align:middle line:84%
between the lower
part of the brain

00:13:35.120 --> 00:13:37.830 align:middle line:84%
and these lower
stages of development.

00:13:37.830 --> 00:13:40.750 align:middle line:84%
However, this lower
brain, it is still

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:43.340 align:middle line:84%
a strong center of
gravity in most of us.

00:13:43.340 --> 00:13:45.970 align:middle line:84%
And it has its hooks
in all of this.

00:13:45.970 --> 00:13:48.555 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've heard
90% of our behavior

00:13:48.555 --> 00:13:50.650 align:middle line:84%
is based on that
lower brain thinking.

00:13:50.650 --> 00:13:52.020 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: That's exactly it.

00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:56.130 align:middle line:84%
And so getting energy into
that prefrontal cortex,

00:13:56.130 --> 00:13:58.870 align:middle line:84%
into that untapped
part of the brain,

00:13:58.870 --> 00:14:03.240 align:middle line:84%
I believe is the key not only
to be able to accelerate,

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:07.630 align:middle line:84%
or evolve, consciousness
in us, but it's also

00:14:07.630 --> 00:14:10.770 align:middle line:84%
how we're going to create that
next epoch, that next stage

00:14:10.770 --> 00:14:14.570 align:middle line:84%
of cultural development,
or human consciousness.

00:14:14.570 --> 00:14:17.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You would explain why
personal development doesn't

00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:20.126 align:middle line:84%
work on most people, why new-age
thinking doesn't work on most

00:14:20.126 --> 00:14:21.750 align:middle line:84%
people because you
can't take a purpose

00:14:21.750 --> 00:14:24.100 align:middle line:84%
and plant it into the
survival center of the brain.

00:14:24.100 --> 00:14:24.410 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: That's it.

00:14:24.410 --> 00:14:25.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It won't work.

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:26.333 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: You better believe it.

00:14:26.333 --> 00:14:27.070 align:middle line:90%
It won't work.

00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:30.200 align:middle line:84%
And we have kind of
a little catchphrase

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:32.420 align:middle line:84%
we like to use regarding
the lower brain.

00:14:32.420 --> 00:14:36.330 align:middle line:84%
And to the lower brain,
sameness equals safety.

00:14:36.330 --> 00:14:39.200 align:middle line:84%
The lower brain wants
your life to be the same.

00:14:39.200 --> 00:14:41.150 align:middle line:84%
And understand, below
the conscious threshold,

00:14:41.150 --> 00:14:42.392 align:middle line:90%
it's dominating your life.

00:14:42.392 --> 00:14:43.850 align:middle line:84%
You don't even know
it's happening.

00:14:43.850 --> 00:14:44.975 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it fears change.

00:14:44.975 --> 00:14:46.220 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: It fears change.

00:14:46.220 --> 00:14:47.310 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:14:47.310 --> 00:14:49.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, imagine
100,000 years ago,

00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:53.340 align:middle line:84%
you're living in a cave as
this caveman and cave woman.

00:14:53.340 --> 00:14:56.666 align:middle line:90%


00:14:56.666 --> 00:14:59.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And the cave
crumbles from something.

00:14:59.270 --> 00:15:00.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's threatening
your survival.

00:15:00.890 --> 00:15:01.700 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: It is.

00:15:01.700 --> 00:15:03.480 align:middle line:84%
Or you have to go
and get food, OK?

00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:05.060 align:middle line:84%
You have to get
food for your clan.

00:15:05.060 --> 00:15:07.330 align:middle line:84%
So you go out of the
cave, and let's say

00:15:07.330 --> 00:15:08.574 align:middle line:90%
there's five paths out there.

00:15:08.574 --> 00:15:09.740 align:middle line:90%
And this is your first time.

00:15:09.740 --> 00:15:11.010 align:middle line:84%
It's a new cave
that you've found.

00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:12.330 align:middle line:84%
It's your first time
out of the cave.

00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:13.630 align:middle line:84%
Your family is in
there with you.

00:15:13.630 --> 00:15:14.130 align:middle line:90%
You go out.

00:15:14.130 --> 00:15:15.070 align:middle line:90%
There's five paths.

00:15:15.070 --> 00:15:16.670 align:middle line:90%
You turn left down a path.

00:15:16.670 --> 00:15:17.860 align:middle line:90%
You walk about 100 yards.

00:15:17.860 --> 00:15:20.900 align:middle line:84%
A sabre toothed tiger comes over
the ridge and tries to eat you.

00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:22.200 align:middle line:90%
And you run as fast as you can.

00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:23.267 align:middle line:90%
And you jump in the cave.

00:15:23.267 --> 00:15:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, the first thing that
the lower brain did was

00:15:25.350 --> 00:15:28.660 align:middle line:84%
register you are not turning
left ever again, right?

00:15:28.660 --> 00:15:30.310 align:middle line:84%
The next morning
you're starving.

00:15:30.310 --> 00:15:31.430 align:middle line:90%
Your family is starving.

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:32.340 align:middle line:90%
You have to go out.

00:15:32.340 --> 00:15:33.756 align:middle line:90%
You're somewhat scared.

00:15:33.756 --> 00:15:35.630 align:middle line:84%
You go out, and there's
all these paths here.

00:15:35.630 --> 00:15:37.713 align:middle line:84%
And you say OK, what's the
furthest one from left?

00:15:37.713 --> 00:15:39.500 align:middle line:84%
I'll take the furthest
one to the right.

00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:41.010 align:middle line:90%
You walk right, you walk down.

00:15:41.010 --> 00:15:44.490 align:middle line:84%
And now this path is much
more rocky than the other one.

00:15:44.490 --> 00:15:46.050 align:middle line:84%
Your feet are now
getting bruised up,

00:15:46.050 --> 00:15:47.200 align:middle line:90%
and they're getting bloody.

00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:48.267 align:middle line:90%
But you keep on walking.

00:15:48.267 --> 00:15:50.100 align:middle line:84%
You keep on going, and
now you're in briars.

00:15:50.100 --> 00:15:52.120 align:middle line:84%
And the briars are
cutting your body up.

00:15:52.120 --> 00:15:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And now you're in this mucky
swamp, and it smells horrible,

00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:55.800 align:middle line:90%
but you keep going.

00:15:55.800 --> 00:15:57.830 align:middle line:84%
You get to this
clearing over there

00:15:57.830 --> 00:15:59.770 align:middle line:84%
where you're having to
pick these berries out

00:15:59.770 --> 00:16:01.936 align:middle line:84%
of these thorny trees that
are cutting your arms up.

00:16:01.936 --> 00:16:04.970 align:middle line:84%
And you get enough berries to
eat and go back to your cave.

00:16:04.970 --> 00:16:08.290 align:middle line:84%
So you go back exactly the
same way, cutting your feet up.

00:16:08.290 --> 00:16:12.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, two days later when
you're starving again,

00:16:12.210 --> 00:16:14.300 align:middle line:84%
and you have to go
get food, are you

00:16:14.300 --> 00:16:16.580 align:middle line:90%
going to go to the far left?

00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:17.250 align:middle line:90%
No way.

00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:18.708 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a
tiger over there.

00:16:18.708 --> 00:16:22.187 align:middle line:84%
And the lower brain is not
going to let you go there.

00:16:22.187 --> 00:16:22.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:24.145 align:middle line:84%
>>COTTON: And it's
also not going

00:16:24.145 --> 00:16:27.700 align:middle line:84%
to let you take a chance on
any of those other paths.

00:16:27.700 --> 00:16:31.190 align:middle line:84%
It's going to say we're going to
go right, even if your feet get

00:16:31.190 --> 00:16:36.207 align:middle line:84%
cut up, even if your body gets
cut up because it did not--

00:16:36.207 --> 00:16:37.665 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because it
didn't kill you.

00:16:37.665 --> 00:16:38.873 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: It didn't kill you.

00:16:38.873 --> 00:16:39.570 align:middle line:90%
You got berries.

00:16:39.570 --> 00:16:40.230 align:middle line:90%
You got food.

00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:41.170 align:middle line:90%
You fed your family.

00:16:41.170 --> 00:16:42.962 align:middle line:84%
And that's all the
lower brain cares about.

00:16:42.962 --> 00:16:44.961 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This would explain
repeating bad habits,

00:16:44.961 --> 00:16:46.250 align:middle line:90%
dysfunctional relationships.

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:47.450 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: That's exactly it.

00:16:47.450 --> 00:16:48.470 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly it.

00:16:48.470 --> 00:16:51.140 align:middle line:84%
And in the modern world,
how that plays out

00:16:51.140 --> 00:16:55.420 align:middle line:84%
is that in our relationships,
in our finances,

00:16:55.420 --> 00:16:59.550 align:middle line:84%
our intellectual brain says
oh, I want to have more money.

00:16:59.550 --> 00:17:02.240 align:middle line:84%
Or I don't want to be in
this rotten relationship.

00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:04.589 align:middle line:84%
Or I hate the
condition of my body.

00:17:04.589 --> 00:17:06.500 align:middle line:84%
Or I don't like
feeling this way.

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:09.520 align:middle line:84%
The lower brain
says that's perfect.

00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:10.849 align:middle line:90%
You woke up alive.

00:17:10.849 --> 00:17:11.349 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:11.349 --> 00:17:12.780 align:middle line:90%
>>COTTON: That was our job.

00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:14.839 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
do it again tomorrow.

00:17:14.839 --> 00:17:18.397 align:middle line:84%
And so you set new goals, new
